5291, "CF ANIL CAMERON - HMS ARIA"

5292, "CAMERON"

5293, "Bonjour Capitaine. Le Commandement de la Couronne a besoin de vos compétences. Vous serez sous mes ordres en tant que responsable des opérations pour la prochaine mission."

5294, "(fr)Katherine Lau has accepted the terms of our contract of employment. I thought it prudent you receive a personalised briefing. You're still a King's Officer, half-pay leave or no."

5295, "(fr)First, a summary of the strategic situation and how it relates to our upcoming operation."

5296, "(fr)As you no doubt know, an unknown actor has been supplying the Malikans with high grade weapons, and setting them loose in Sulsia."

5297, "(fr)It's clear the intent must have been to cripple the Sulsian Hegemony, and as a result undermine Commonwealth interests in the sector."

5298, "(fr)We don't know exactly who's supplying them, but we believe high ranking officers within the Sinarus Combine are involved."

5299, "(fr)The consequences have been severe. The Sulsian navy has been brought to its knees, and thousands of civilians in Sulsia have died at the hands of Andri Gadaria's militia."

5300, "(fr)For his crimes against humanity, the Alban Commonwealth has answered the Sulsian Hegemony's call for assistance to bring Andri Gadaria to justice."

5301, "(fr)Crown Command has identified two short-term goals in the Sulsian theatre. First is to apprehend or neutralise Gadaria."

5302, "(fr)Second is to identify the individual responsible for arming Gadaria's terrorist group and gather evidence against them."

5303, "(fr)The Alban Parliament is building a coalition against the Sinarus Combine. The more evidence we can bring to the table, the more support we can gather and the better we can offset the Combine's military power."

5304, "(fr)When war comes to the Commonwealth, we'll need all the advantage we can get."

5305, "(fr)All right Ross, Meiks. Your former masters have hired us for an operation against the Sinarus Combine. I figure since we're already enemies with their rear admirals we might as well go all in."

5306, "(fr)Commander Cameron's crew has finished their interrogation of Kendra. She doesn't know who her employer was but was able to give details of their intermediary."

5307, "(fr)Through Kendra's information, the Albans have identified a convoy which could give clues to her employer's identity."

5308, "(fr)The convoy contains three Sinarus-flagged freighters with a cruiser escort. Their destination is Guardador Station, a mining hub in Sulsia that was comandeered by the Malikans several days ago."

5309, "(fr)The cargo manifest on those freighters mentions heavy mining equipment but the Albans believe they're shipping weapons under cover."

5310, "(fr)The Albans want one of the freighters so they can dissect her cargo for clues. This is where we come in."

5311, "(fr)The Hoshikuzu will jump in just inside ASM range of the convoy and launch missile strikes against the convoy's escorts. The hope is that the Combine warships are lured into an engagement away from their charges."

5312, "(fr)Once an opening is made, you need to disable the astrogation systems of one of the freighters. This is critical. We cannot commit the rest of our group until we're sure the freighters won't be able to make a run for it."

5313, "(fr)Once this is done we'll call in the Nassau, Hopewell and the Aria to assault the Combine ships."

5314, "(fr)This is going to be a balancing act. As long as the Combine think they're dealing with a solitary corvette, they'll be less inclined to warp out."

5315, "(fr)One more thing you two should know. The Hoshi's drone bay got replaced by her ASM launcher, so you won't have any repair drones for the first part of the mission. Be careful out there."

5316, "(fr)I think that's it. Probably the most insane job I've ever accepted, but your Commander Cameron is paying us premium rates. It helps that I've got you two with me to help pull this through."

; m21_vn.txt

5317, "(fr)I got an urgent communication from Admiral Bertini's office. The old bulldog wants us flying alongside his flagship against the Malikans. He's got firm intel on Gadaria's location and he wants blood."

5318, "(fr)The terrorist leader has been tracked to Jotram station, the logistical, military and spiritual heart of the Malika People's Militia. The place is a fortress, but Bertini wants us to crack it open."

5319, "(fr)The Sulsians didn't say why Gadaria withdrew back home after spending months in the front lines, though I'd bet good money the inbound Commonwealth battle group's got something to do with it."

5320, "(fr)It doesn't matter. The Sulsian navy has been crippled by months of Malikan hit and run attacks and most ships have been destroyed or are under repair. Admiral Bertini needs escort ships for the attack on Jotram Station."

5321, "(fr)Bertini's primary objective is to locate Andri Gadaria and bring him to justice."

5322, "(fr)Fringe law is relatively straightforward in this regard. Justice for the Sulsians means death, whether it's through a court-sentenced execution or missile warheads."

5323, "(fr)I've accepted his contract. I didn't even negotiate a higher payment. If Bertini wants to send Gadaria to hell, I'm one hundred percent on board."

5324, "(fr)Jotram Station is the hub of asteroid mining operations in the system. It was the site of the first worker rebellion that birthed the Malika People's Militia."

5325, "(fr)Bertini plans for it to be the site where the Militia dies."

5326, "(fr)Sulsian intelligence on the station is comprehensive. Jotram is heavily guarded by the cruisers Yama and Virago, and a screen of smaller corvettes."

5327, "(fr)The Protogénie is the sole remaining heavy unit of the Sulsian Navy and will be the backbone of the assault. The Hoshikuzu and Nassau is to provide CIWS support against Malikan gunships and ASMs."

5328, "(fr)Bertini assures me the Protogénie can eat the smaller Malikan ships for breakfast. What the battlecruiser can't do is counter small strike craft and missiles. We'll just have to do that for her."

5329, "(fr)Last time the Hoshikuzu faced off against Gadaria's ships, she was a converted transport with only a few light cannons as armament. This time she's a fully armed warship, and she's got friends."

5330, "(fr)It's time to buckle up. Today the Hoshi and Nassau go to war."

; m22_vn.txt

5331, "(fr)Lieutenant Ross. My congratulations on your victory at Jotram Station. The entire operation was a risk but Bertini was never a man of temperance."

5332, "(fr)The strategic situation in Sulsia remains volatile. We've received word that the Children of Renewal congregation is heading for the Pallavian Veil via Sulsian space."

5333, "(fr)We believe this is one reason why the Malikans have halted their advance and pulled back. We're unsure how the Children of Renewal prompted this, as they have no military capacity to threaten Gadaria."

5334, "(fr)Admiral Cleghorn has authorised a light unit detachment to shadow the Renewal congregation. Due to the proximity of the Veil to Sulsia, we need to identify any possible threats to future Commonwealth operations here."

5335, "(fr)I want your ships with me. Our task is to escort the Renewal convoy to it's destination and discover their intentions there."

5336, "(fr)Your Katherine Lau already has a professional relationship with Reverend Lightowler on Alliance, and I plan to take full advantage of this."

5337, "(fr)I've contacted Reverend Lightowler. He's given us the coordinates of the Renewal's final destination. It's deep within the Pallavian Veil, off of all major cartographical charts."

5338, "(fr)This is the location of the Children of Renewal's 'Promised Land'. They're making the final journey with their entire contingent."

5339, "(fr)I've checked our long range sensors. There's a black hole orbiting a K-type star, but no detectable planets or other system bodies. Lightowler assures me the coordinates correspond to high orbit of an Earth-like planet."

5340, "(fr)It's possible the black hole or the Veil itself is confounding our long range sensors. If there is a planet out there, we might not be able to see it."

5341, "(fr)The Children of Renewal have shared their space charts with us. If we need to make our way out without Alliance, we'll be able to use their navigation data."

5342, "(fr)I suspect this is the last job that the Renewal are offering us. Lightowler's offering an astronomical payment for this job, enough for me, Navo and Badami to retire comfortably and the rest of our group to receive a generous payout."

5343, "(fr)I don't know if this 'Promised Land' is real. I suppose it doesn't matter. It's real enough to the Children of Renewal and that's good enough for my conscience."

5344, "(fr)DODO MEIKS - LADIGUE STATION"

5345, "(fr)MEIKS"

